A Honduran judge has authorized the extradition of former President Juan Orlando Hernandez to the U.S. to stand trial on drug trafficking and weapon charges, Reuters has reported. Hernandez, who was arrested mid-February this year following the U.S. extradition request, has three days to appeal the judge's decision, according to a judicial spokesperson. (Cover: Former Honduran President Juan Orlando Hernandez spoke at the UN Climate Change Conference (COP26) in Glasgow, Britain, November 1, 2021. /Reuters)